Text: Al Horford giving it up to the Hawks fans in his postgame interview.
Hawks make it 4 in a row, drop Pacers 109-100 at Philips Arena. Lou Will has 21 to lead six Hawks in double figures. #ATLHawks #teameffort
Make that 8 of the Hawks' last 10 for Teague. #TeagueTakeover
Teague taking over down the stretch at the Highlight Factory. 6 straight for him and the Hawks lead is back to 11, 101-90. #ATLHawks
Al Horford stops a Pacers run with the jumper, then forces a tie ball on the other end. 93-88 #ATLHawks, 4:51 to play.
John Jenkins gets the breakaway layin, and he's into double-digits for the first time in his career. 88-80 #ATLhawks
Ivan Johnson gets a huge reaction from the crowd as he exits with 8:09 to play. #dontmesswithIvan
Ivan Johnson freight-trains down the lane for the hoop and the foul. #ATLHawks #dontmesswithIvan
Lou Williams also has 16, to go with a career-high 11 assists. #ATLHawks
At the end of 3Q, the Hawks lead the Pacers 83-70. Horford and Korver with 16 each. #ATLHawks #fourthquarter
On the ensuing Pacers possession, Zaza grabs a defensive rebound for the double-double as well. Indy needs a TO, and its 79-65 #ATLHawks
Korver hits a long 3, and with the assist Lou Williams nabs his first career double-double. #jobwelldoneLou #ATLHawks
LouWill hits a long 3, and how he, Zaza, and Al each have 14 to lead the team. 72-65 #ATLHawks
Lou Williams hits the long 2, and he's now 1 assist shy of his first career double-double. #ATLHawks #nojinx
4 more points for Zaza, who now has 12 points and 9 rebounds. 62-54 #ATLHawks
Kyle Korver knocks down the long three for the Hawks' first bucket of the second half. 3-3 from distance for KK now. 58-50 #ATLHawks
Back at it for the second half. Original starters on the floor for ATL. #ATLHawks
Excellent 1st half for ATL, as they lead 55-48 at the break. Horford has 14, Lou Will has 9 and 9 assists, three with 8. #ATLHawks
3 straight buckets by Zaza Pachulia, and Hawks lead is out to 52-43. Pacers take a TO. #ATLHawks
Horford spins inside for another basket. Big Al has 14 in the first half now on 7-8 from the field. 46-43 #ATLHawks
Jenkins making the most of his PT, shakes Tyler Hansbrough for the step-back 3, and he's got 8. 40-33 #ATLHawks
End of 1Q, and Hawks lead 33-26. Team is on FIRE, shooting 70% in the period. #ATLHawks
John Jenkins comes off the screen for the silky-smooth jumper. Then hits the wide-open 3! 29-20 #ATLHawks #rookonfire
Ivan Johnson and DeShawn Stevenson check in after missing last night's contest in Cleveland. John Jenkins in as well. 21-18 #ATLHawks

Text: @CSU_Vikes Thanks Carrie. Good game tonight!
Photos from the #ATLHawks' 3rd straight win: http://t.co/xh6Et11M
Tonight's win improves Atlanta's road record to 8-4, the best in the Eastern Conference! Go #ATLHawks!
#ATLHawks win!!! A big 4th quarter for the Hawks as they get a 102-94 win in Cleveland. They're now 8-4 on the road.
KYLE KORVER FOR 3!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! #ATLHawks lead 100-94 on a CLUTCH 3 by Kyle! 1:21 to go!
Sweaty palms time in Cleveland! Teague's jumper gives the #ATLHawks a 95-94 lead with 2:24 left!
You all have been calling for Jenkins...he's delivering in this 4th quarter! #ATLHawks
Timeout on the floor. Teague's steal and dunk gives the #ATLHawks an 83-82 lead with 8:11 left. LET'S GO HAWKS!
John Jenkins gets the 4th quarter start and kisses one off the window to pull the #ATLHawks within 3! #RookieEffort
#ATLHawks having trouble closing quarters strong tonight. #Cavs lead 80-75 going into the 4th.
Back-to-back 3's by Korver!!! #HotSauce
Teague's 3 pointer stops the bleeding and pulls the #ATLHawks within 6 halfway through the 3rd quarter.
The #Cavs started the second half the way the #ATLHawks started the first - with the first 6 points. Hawks trail 60-55.
The #Cavs end the first half on a circus shot by Kyrie Irving to close within 1.  55-54 #ATLHawks at the break.
The story of this first half is ANTHONY TOLLIVER! He has 11 points, 3 boards and just took a charge! #ATLHawks
Tolliver has 7 points tonight...he had only 42 all season. #Sparkplug #ATLHawks
Timeout #Cavs after Teague gets a layup. He has 14 to spark an 8-0 run and push the lead back to 5. Let's go #ATLHawks!!!
After the starters scored the first 25, Tolliver hits a 3 for the #ATLHawks. Teague follows with a 3 of his own.
Neither team playing great defense...we go to the 2nd quarter with the #ATLHawks down 26-25. Teague leads a balanced scoring effort with 9.
Pachulia and Morrow enter for the #ATLHawks after the starters played the first 11 minutes. 23-22 Hawks.
How good has Larry Drew been out of timeouts? Horford gets an easy dunk on the pass from Smith. #ATLHawks
#Cavs put together a nice run after the 8-0 #ATLHawks start. Timeout Hawks as Cleveland leads 11-10.
Horford, Teague, Smith and Korver each have a bucket...it's 8-0 #ATLHawks early!!!
#ATLHawks win the tip but Smith misses the first shot and we're underway against the #Cavs
What will be the final score of tonight's game? Post your predictions here: http://t.co/lmUAog8r #ATLHawks

Text: Kyle Korver ices it at the line with 2 FTs to make it 124-116 with 17.1 to play. #ATLHawks
Kyle Korver, who couldn't hit a basket all night, comes up with the clutch 3, and the Hawks now lead 120-114. #makesemwhenweneedem
Jeff Teague down the lane for another bucket! 117-112 with 2:00 left in 2OT. #BringithomeHawks
Hawks guards coming up clutch in 2OT - Lou Williams draws the charge on Rodney Stuckey. #ATLHawks
...and it stands! Teague to the line for the pair of FTs, and Hawks will have the ball up 115-112. #ATLHawks
Hawks force the TO, and refs call a clear path foul on Pistons. One more time to the video review... #ATLHawks
Much needed trey from Jeff Teague puts Hawks back out front. 113-112 with 2:30 to play. #ATLHawks
Tired bodies on both teams out on the floor now. Lou Williams gets to the line, hits a pair. 110-108 #ATLHawks.
Josh Smith misses just short at the buzzer, and we're heading to double-OT at Philips. #ATLHawks #crazygame
Josh Smith Ds up Will Bynum, forces the miss. Hawks ball, 3.3 to play in OT. #ATLHawks #letsdothis
Teague explodes to the rim, gets fouled. Hits both, tied at 108. #ATLHawks
Horford gets the bucket out of the TO, then Hawks force the shot-clock violation. ATL ball down 108-106, 1:09 to play.
Bynum hits two straight for Pistons, and Hawks trail 108-104 with 1:41 to play. #ATLHawks
BIG three from the corner from Lou Williams, and Hawks reclaim the lead 104-103 with 2:41 left in OT. #ATLHawks
Another video review at Philips. Initial ruling Hawks ball out of bounds, but review shows ball belongs to Pistons. 103-101 Detroit.
Horford misses the second, and we're heading to OT at Philips Arena. #ATLHawks
Al hits the first. Tied at 101.
Al Horford with daylight heading to the hole, gets tackled by entire Pistons defense with 1.8 seconds left. Al has 2 FTs for the tie/win.
Austin Daye hits a 3-pointer and the Pistons now lead 101-100 with 4.0 seconds left. Time to dig deep. #ATLHawks
Replay was inconclusive, and the goaltend stands. 100-96 #ATLHawks
The refs call goaltend on Josh Smith, but now they are going to take a look at it. #ATLHawks
Former Ga Tech standout Will Bynum ripping the nets for the Pistons tonight. 4-6 from downtown. #GAlove
7 straight points for Anthony Morrow. He's got 12 in the second half, 16 overall. 91-74 #ATLHawks, 7:33 to play.
Anthony Morrow hits the jumper, then a 3 and he's now the 3rd Hawk player in double-digits with 14. 89-71 Hawks. #ATLHawks
Hawks shoot 77% from the field in the 3Q, outscoring Pistons 31-17 in the process. #ATLHawks
DeShawn Stevenson nails a 3, and the Hawks have their biggest lead of the game at the end of 3Q at 81-62. #ATLHawks #fourthquarter
At the timeout, Hawks lead 76-62 after @MrAnthonyMorrow 3 in transition. #ATLHawks

Marquis Teague (Jeff's little bro) is on the court with Jeff right now. #WaitYourTurnLittleBro #NotInOurHouse

#ATLHawks have 66 points with three minutes left in the third quarter...FROM THE STARTERS!

The #ATLHawks are ballin' tonight! Teague's three & Horford's jumper pushes the lead to 21! It's 66-45 HAWKS!

Text: Some photos from tonight's game against the #Sixers: http://t.co/UOexlTO9
Final Score: Sixers 99, #ATLHawks 80... Smith had 17 pts, Lou Williams had 13 and Kyle Korver had 11
TO with 3:22 left in the 4th, Sixers lead the #ATLHawks, 88-74. Jenkins and Scott seeing some court time and both have scored #ATLHawks
End of the 3rd, #ATLHawks trail the Sixers 72-64. We're still in this #ATLHawks fans! Who steps up in the 4th to be the difference maker?
Lou Williams drains a 3-pointer, #ATLHawks trail the Sixers, 69-56, with 2 minutes left in the 3rd
Sixers open the 2nd half with a 10-4 run, #ATLHawks call a TO, Sixers lead the Hawks, 61-49
Zaza hits the jumper from a pass from Lou Will, Sixers 51, #ATLHawks 45 at the break
Back-to-back 3's from Teague and then Korver bring the #ATLHawks within 1, Sixers 43, Hawks 42. Let's go #ATLHawks!
#ATLHawks call a TO, Sixers up 42-36 with 4:46 left in the 1st half
Zaza with back-to-back-to-back shots and a free throw shot in there too! Sixers 32, #ATLHawks 30
End of the 1st qtr, Sixers lead the #ATLHawks, 30-23. Josh Smith leads the way with 13 points and 4 rbds
Lou Will at the line after making the shot... Hits the FT, #ATLHawks down 20-16
Josh Smith with the put-back off a missed Lou Will shot, #ATLHawks trail 20-11
And with that thank you message, Lou is on the floor... Mix of "Boo's" and "Lou's" I think! Let's go #ATLHawks!
Sixers just played a thank you message to Lou Williams on the jumbotron here at Wells Fargo Center #class #ATLHawks
Kyle Korver with the first 3 of the game... Game knotted at 7-7 #ATLHawks
#ATLHawks win the tip and the game is underway here in Philly!
Alright #ATLHawks fans, as we run down the clock until tip-off here in Philly, let's get some top scorer predictions... Ready. Set. Go!
Starters for your #ATLHawks: Stevenson, Smith, Horford, Korver & Teague. For the Sixers: Turner, Young, Allen, Richardson & Holiday
Lou Will perfecting his shot... Sixers fans all giving Lou a warm welcome here at Wells Fargo Center #ATLHawks http://t.co/YPXuK0pR
@_tiffftifff Thanks!
From Lou Will: "They (Sixers) have been struggling lately but they've got a lot of talent, this cannot be a game we take lightly" #ATLHawks
MT @CBSOutdoor: #ATLHawks taking over #Atlanta Transit! The wrapped bus is hard to miss and catches eyes everywhere! http://t.co/EBaHw6DK

Text: Big 3-pointer from Kyle Korver cuts it to 90-83. Hawks need stops! #ATLHawks
Love the patience right there from Josh Smith on the block. Waits for the double team to come, then finds Lou Williams for the 3. 77-72 OKC.
Anthony Tolliver throws it down on the break! Hawks back within 4! #ATLHawks #comeback
Great run by the Hawks to end 3Q. 12-2 run makes it 73-66 Thunder as we start the final 12. #ATLHawks #fourthquarter
Beautiful alley-oop from Josh Smith to LouWill, and Zaza follows with an putback! 73-66, fans coming alive at Philips! #LetsgoHawks

Text: Photos from tonight's overtime VICTORY: http://t.co/asbIVSjD Go #ATLHawks!
Great defense by the Hawks! Josh Smith comes from behind for the block on Nene, and Kyle Korver looks to finish it off at the foul line.
Timeout Wizards, and Hawks lead 98-95 with 24 seconds left in OT. One more defensive stop, and we all go home victorious. #ATLHawks
BIG three by DeShawn Stevenson, and he breaks out the "cant feel my face" for the Wizards fans #ATLHawks
Lou Williams to the line for a pair of FTs, hits one of two and we're tied at 93-93 with 2:27 to play in OT. #ATLHawks
Sorry, that foul was on Kyle Korver, and he now has 5. #ATLHawks
Josh Smith called for the foul on Nene. He's got 5 now as well. #ATLHawks
Jordan Crawford comes up short on the buzzer-beater, and we're headed to overtime in DC. #ATLHawks #freebasketball
Jeff Teague called for an offensive foul getting into the lane with 2.7 seconds left. 5 on him. #ATLHawks #forceOT
Earl Barron hits the J to tie it at 90-90, and Hawks will have the ball with :23 left and chance to take final shot. #ATLHawks #crunchtime
Lou Williams sticks the huge 3, and Hawks lead 90-88 with 30 seconds to play. #ATLHawks
Big rebound and follow dunk by Smoove gives the Hawks the lead, 87-85. #ATLHawks
Crunch time now. Tied at 85-85, 2:29 to play in the game. Let's go #ATLHawks!
End of 3, and Hawks up 72-69 over the Wizards. Lou Williams and Josh Smith both have 13 points. #ATLHawks
Ivan Johnson back in for the first time since getting stitches earlier in 1st half. #ATLHawks
DeShawn Stevenson checking in for the Wizards, and gets a nice chorus of boos from the DC crowd. #ATLHawks
Smoove's block gets the defense in gear - two straight steals, two straight breakaway dunks. 65-58 #ATLHawks with 4:31 to play in 3Q.
Wow. What a block by Smoove. Beal went skyward, and Josh Smith DENIED it. #ATLHawks
Jordan Crawford and Jeff Teague continuing the conversation, get the double tech from Joey Crawford. #norelation
Jordan Crawford heating up for the Wiz, and letting the Hawks bench know about it. #dontpokethebearJordan
Back at it for Hawks-Wiz second half. Anthony Tolliver in for Devin Harris along with other four starters. #ATLHawks
Update on Devin Harris. Sore left foot, won't return tonight. #ATLHawks
At the half, Hawks lead the Wizards 52-46. Korver leads with 10, Smoove has 9, Harris/Teague/LouWill with 8 each. #ATLHawks
Ivan Johnson got 4 stitches between his right pinky and 4th finger. Guess who is still going to return nonetheless? #dontmesswithIvan
Kyle Korver hits another trey - 3 3's on the night for him, and hasn't missed yet. A team-leading 9 points for KK. 44-38 #ATLHawks
Neither looked serious, but we'll update when we know more.
Tough stretch there for the Hawks, as Ivan Johnson and Devin Harris both retreating to the locker room to get checked out.
Hawks have the offensive game working despite some early TOs, shoot 57.9% in 1Q for 28-22 lead at the quarter break. #ATLHawks
Ivan Johnson in the game, immediately hits the long 2-pt jumper. #ATLHawks #dontmesswithIvan
Josh Smith going after it after his rought night against the Warriors. Already has 3 buckets, all within a couple feet of the basket.
What he said. RT @JustinJumpstart: If you leave Korver wide open for three, he will make it! #guaranteed #ATLHawks

Text: Tonight's win was a total team victory. That and more quick thoughts after the #ATLHawks win: http://t.co/vB5PjrYi
Photos of the FIRST PLACE #ATLHawks beating the Bobcats? Yes please: http://t.co/czd9hTWK
6 players in double figures tonight for Hawks, led by Devin Harris with 20 and Smoove with 18. 57.3% shooting from the field on the night!
Jenkins hits a 3, and Mike Scott follows with a jumper of his own to finish out the scoring. 113-90 your final at Philips! #ATLHawks #win
John Jenkins with the smooth release on the step-back J. #ATLHawks
Rookie time! Mike Scott and John Jenkins check in for the Hawks up 106-84 with 4:20 to play.
Lou Williams with the breakaway dunk, and Hawks nearing the century mark. 97-76 with 9:53 to play. #ATLHawks
@JWinfro Liking his chances!
End of the 3Q, and Hawks cruising 91-74. Lou Williams has tied his career high with 9 assists off the bench. #ATLHawks #sharingthewealth
Ivan Johnson in the game with 2 straight buckets. Everyone getting in on the act tonight. 82-60 #ATLHawks, 3:35 left in 3Q
My goodness. Two straight 3s for DeShawn Stevenson, and Hawks lead up to 74-48. ATL 11/19 from downtown. #ATLHawks #hothothot
To work on in second half: Hawks shooting 60% from field, 50% from FT line. #ATLHawks #neverstopimproving
Couldn't ask for much more in a half. Hawks lead 60-43 at the break. ATL shooting 59.5%, CHA shooting 35.9%. Devin leads #ATLHawks.with 16.
DeShawn Stevenson just came dangerously close to scoring from inside the arc. He passed it off to Horford for the bucket instead. #pheew
Harris and Smoove force turnover, and Devin glides in for the layup, now has 14 points on 5-5 from the field. Bobcats TO, Hawks lead 48-31
Hawks on FIRE right now. Devin Harris 3 puts ATL up 45-28. Shooting 59.3% from the field in first half. #ATLHawks #enfuego
Balance is the key for the #ATLHawks right now. 15 points from the bench has helped spark a 38-24 lead! 8:59 to go in the first half.
Lou Williams heating up early tonight. Two straight 3s for @TeamLou23, and Hawks now lead 26-14. Love the fast start on 2nd night of B2Bs

Text: LD said before the game to expect a deep lineup tonight. Josh Smith now the only starter on the court for the Hawks. 20-12 #ATLHawks

Josh Smith skies for the offensive board and the putback, and the Hawks are on the board. 2-0 #ATLHawks

Text: HAWKS WIN! #ATLHawks 86, Magic 80. Smoove had 16 pts and 11 rbds, while Horford had 13 pts and 13 rbds... Teague (16 pts) Lou Will (11 pts)
#ATLHawks call TO, Hawks are up 84-76 with about 3 minutes left to play... Let's hear some final score predictions #ATLHawks fans...
With 5:23 left to play, #ATLHawks lead the Magic 82-72... Five guys in the double-digits, Teague and Smith with 14 each
Pachulia's offense has come alive here in Orlando....nice drive fakes the pass and lays it in with the foul....Zaza with 7 pts and 8 rbds
At the end of the 3rd qtr, #ATLHawks lead the Magic 72-60... Smoove leads the way with 14 pts, Horford with 13 and Teague with 12
Horford's 13 pts and 10 rbds marks his 7th-straight double-double #ATLHawks
Horford with the two-hand jam!!! #ATLHawks lead the Magic 55-38... Al has 12 pts and 9 rbds
Teague for THREEEE puts the #ATLHawks up 49-36
At the end of the half the #ATLHawks lead 46-34...Josh Smith leads scorers with 10 pts and 4 rbds followed by Horford with 8 pts and 8 rbds
Horford misses his shot but gets the board and puts it back in....#ATLHawks lead 42-34...Al has 8 pts, 7 rbds and 3 asts so far tonight
Korver knocks down another 3 pointer....#ATLHawks lead 40-34...Kyle is 2-for-3 from downtown so far tonight.  #Gladtohaveyouback
At the end of the 1st, your #ATLHawks lead the Magic 20-15. Smoove with 6 pts & Morrow and Harris with 4 pts a piece
After back-to-back shots from Morrow and back-to-back shots from Harris, #ALTHawks with a huge lead, 16-2 with 6:03 left in the 1st qtr
J-Smoove with a putback, #ATLHawks jump out to a 6-0 lead
Aaaand the game is underway at the Amway Center...  Let's go #ATLHawks!
Less than 20 minutes till tip here in Orlando... We want to hear from you #ATLHawks fans - What does Morrow bring to the starting lineup?
Those of you who said Anthony Morrow will be starting tonight are correct! #ATLHawks
Starters for your Hawks tonight vs. ORL: Teague, Harris, Smith, Horford and guess who will be making their first start with the #ATLHawks???
Orlando has asked us for their help tonight. Help the Magic finish this sentence: http://t.co/Qs1zv0ck #ATLHawks
#ATLHawks fans - Join us in wishing NBA legend/Hawk great Bob Pettit a happy 80th birthday today right here: http://t.co/W6nPTegy

Text: Teague with a 3 pointer...#ATLHawks lead 65-63
Al with a nice pass of his own to Josh for the easy lay in...#ATLHawks trail 63-62...Horford with 16 pts and 7 rbds, Josh 15 pts 6 asts
Horford slammed on Wade...#WOW...#ATLHawks tie the game at 56..
@Monienthemiddl_ I noticed you put #ATLHawks first... GO HAWKS!
At the end of the 1st half...#ATLHawks trail 56-54...Smoove leads Atlanta with 13, Deshawn with 12 and Al has 10 points and 5 rebounds
Stevenson hits his 4th 3 pointer of the game and gives the #ATLHawks the 54-53 lead.
The opposing team is shooting 62.5% and we are beating them...#Illtakethat
Smoove 3-for-3 from 3 point land....now has 13 points...#ATLHawks tie the game at 44
6:51 left in the 2nd quarter...#ATLHawks trail 42-41...Josh with 10 points, Al with 8, Deshawn with 6 and Lou with 5 points off the bench
End of the 1st quarter...#ATLHawks trail 28-26....Smoove with 10 points, 3 rebounds and 3 assists leads all scorers.
Smith hits another 3 from the wing...playing like the Eastern Conference Player of THIS Week...#Smoove
Josh buries a 3 from the corner...ties the game at 23...Smith with 7 points and 3 rebounds and 3 assists in the 1st quarter.
Horford missed the memo on all the starters wearing the same shoes....#ItsokAl
Stevenson with another 3 pointer gives the #ATLHawks the lead 14-13...Josh passing the ball very well out of the post tonight.
Stevenson hits the 3 pointer to start the scoring....3-0 #ATLHawks.
Udonis Haslem (flu) is inactive for the Heat... We're ready to get this game started here in Miami... Are you all ready #ATLHawks fans?!?!
Starters for your #ATLHawks: Smith, Horford, Stevenson, Harris & Teague. For the Heat: James, Lewis, Bosh, Wade & Chalmers

Text: @Jaekwon_Jo We see you too Jake! Go #ATLHawks
@JWinfro Show us where you're seeing the national love James? We don't see it. All we know is our fans are loyal and that's what matters!
A few photos from tonight's HUGE win over the #Grizzlies in Memphis: http://t.co/bv899rVw How 'bout them Hawks!
HAWKS WIN! #ATLHawks hand the Grizz just their 2nd home loss of the season defeating them 93-83. Smoove led the way with a game-high 24 pts
The crowd is starting to file out here at FedEx Forum... Under a minute left to play and your #ATLHawks lead 87-78
Lou with a big 3 from the corner....followed by a lay up by Teague....#ATLHawks up 87-75 with 3:03 left in the game.
Smoove hammered on the shot, makes the basket, goes to the line and makes the FT, puts #ATLHawks up 80-71 over the Grizz
Horford drives down the lane for the lay up...Al with 18 points and 10 rebounds on the night.
#ATLHawks up 73-60 with 10:25 left in the 4th quarter...trying to give the Grizzlies just their 2nd home loss of this season.
Don't know who made Lou mad but he scored the final 11 points in the 3rd quarter for the #ATLHawks...#NiceHomecoming
#ATLHawks head into the final qtr leading the Grizz, 73-60. #ATLHawks outscored Memphis 32-13 in the 3rd - Top scorer predictions anyone???
CORRECTION: Lou Will with back-to-back-to-back 3's, #ATLHawks on an 18-0 run - Let's hear you #ATLHawks fans!!!
Lou Will with back-to-back 3's! #ATLHawks up 71-58
#ATLHawks on a nice 12-0 run, now lead the Grizzlies 65-58 with 2:16 left in the 3rd qtr
Smoove drains a three and the #ATLHawks take the lead over the Grizz, 60-58, Let's go Hawks!

DeShawn Stevenson hits another 3. 24 of DeShawn's 28 FGs this season are from distance. 23-15 #ATLHawks!
Hawks starting to force some turnovers on D and get out and run. Devin hits a 3 to put ATL up 16-10 and force a Wizards TO. 16-10 #ATLHawks
Josh Smith gets the offensive rebound and the jam, and Teague follows with a high-arc floater. 8-8 midway through the 1Q. #ATLHawks
Josh Smith hits a J from the corner and the Hawks are on the board. 2-2 here at Philips early on. #ATLHawks
Underway at the Highlight Factory! Teague, DeShawn, Al, Smoove, and Devin in the lineup for #ATLHawks
No TV for tonight's Hawks-Wiz game. Listen to @RealVoiceofHawk on @680_The_Fan , and follow along with us on Twitter for all the action.

Hawks drop a close one to the Grizzlies 
110-102...tune into http://t.co/05aJ27a2 for video recap.
Josh Smith with another lay in to cut the lead to 106-102 Grizzlies...Need a stop.
Josh Smith with the easy lay in with under 2 minutes to play....Hawks down 103-100.
Josh Smith dishes to Al Horford for the lay in...Hawks down 101-98
Al Horford, in regular-season form: http://t.co/tOW3WNDk #ATLHawks
Hawks have 5 guys with double digit scoring..Morrow, Korver and Horford with 11 points...Williams and Johnson with 10 points. 10:03 to go.
Ivan with a strong drive to the hole for the lay in..Hawks down 3...87-84
Lou Williams finds Zaza cutting to the basket for the lay up and the foul...Hawks cut the lead to 5.  87-82 Grizzlies.
4th quarter underway...Let's go Hawks.
End of the 3rd quarter....Grizzlies lead 87-79..Hawks need a big 4th quarter.
Josh Smith with a steal and takes it all the way for the dunk...Hawks cut the lead to 1..77-76 Grizzlies.
Korver knocks down another three to break the tie...Hawks up 72-69
Kyle Korver knocks down the 3 pointer and gets fouled...hits the free throw ...Hawks up 67-61
Hawks have 15 fastbreak points....Grizzlies have 5.
2nd half underway..
Scoring leaders at the half for the Hawks are Horford and Morrow with 11 points each.
End of the 1st half Hawks lead the Grizzies 59-54...#stronghalf
Josh Smith with a rebound and dunk....Hawks lead 59-52
Horford just throws down a thunderous one handed dunk that got the Hawks bench off their seats...#wow
With 3:42 left in the 2nd the Hawks have 51 points....will they break the 100 point mark tonight?
Hawks shooting 57% from the field so far..#keepitup

Text: At the under 6 minute timeout the Hawks lead 44-38.
Nice drive and dish by Teague to Mike Scott for the lay in..Hawks up 41-34.
Timout with 8:30 left in the 2nd...Hawks up 39-32..Grizzlies must have eaten too much BBQ...
Anthony Morrow with 11 points and Ivan Johnson with 8 points to lead the Hawks in the 1st quarter.
End of the 1st quarter and the Hawks are up 33-25.
Morrow knocks down a floater..He has 11 points in the 1st quarter..Hawks lead 33-23.
Morrow hits the open 3 pointer on the break...Hawks lead 29-19..#greatstart
Lou Will with a smooth lay in and the foul...Makes the free throw for the 3-point play...Hawks up 21-13.
Morrow knocks down the 3 pointer on the break...Hawks lead 18-7 with 6:07 to play in the 1st.
Kyle Korver has gotten in on the scoring for the Hawks with a 3 ball...Hawks lead 13-2.
Ivan knocks down 2 free throws...8 points on the night already with over 7 minutes left in the 1st.
Grizzlies timeout...Hawks looking good early up 8-0 with 8:34 to go in the 1st Quarter.
Must be Ivan's night...he hits a baseline jumper..6-0 Hawks.
Hawks running the court....Ivan with another lay in...4-0 Hawks
Teague nice dish to Ivan for the lay in...Hawks on the board first. 2-0 Hawks.
#ATLHawks win the tip and the game is underway.
@ATLHawks Not until the season starts but we will be live tweeting all game...tip-off in 13 minutes. #staytuned

Text: Postgame thoughts on the Hawks close 101-99 loss to the Spurs: http://t.co/FQQDNRCj
Welp. Nando Di Colo hits a jumper with 0.6 left, and Damion James' heave falls short. Hawks fall 101-99. Scott leads with 11. #ATLHawks
MIKE SCOTT FOR 3!!! 99-99 with 4.0 seconds left. #ATLHawks #freebasketball?
Cory Joseph misses two FTs with 6.2 seconds, and Hawks call TO. Will have ball down 3. Tony Parker is running the huddle on the Spurs bench.
There is a heckler behind the Hawks bench, heckling the team during a preseason game. #silliness #ATLHawks
Mike Scott gets a bucket, and Hawks force a turnover. Down 3, final possession to come... #ATLHawks
Will Witherspoon answers for Spurs with a 3, and Hawks trail 99-94 with 33.2. Hawks call timeout #ATLHawks
Benson gets the rebound, and Mike Scott nails a jumper. It's tight! 96-94 Spurs, under 45 seconds to play #ATLHawks
Hawks not out of this yet. Have the ball down 94-90 with 2:42 left. #ATLHawks
Keith Benson gets another bucket, then a block, and the Hawks bench is LOVING it. Love to see that kind of cameraderie. #ATLHawks
Oh man - Isma'il Muhammad just flew in baseline and was about to wreck it before Eddy Curry knocked him down. 94-88 Spurs. #ATLHawks
Spurs on a little mini-run and Hawks call timeout, trailing 90-85 with 5:08 to play. #ATLHawks
Benson with another basket inside, makes a nice adjustment in midair to avoid the block. 86-85 Spurs with 6:21 left. #ATLHawks
Lou Williams in to lead the youngsters, and zips a sweet pass inside to Benson for another dunk. 83-82 Hawks with 8:34 to play. #ATLHawks
Keith Benson and Isma'il Muhammad get their first action, and every Hawk that dressed has played tonight. Benson flushes for 2. #ATLHawks
John Jenkins showing his sweet stroke tonight - hits another 3, and Hawks lead 73-71 to end the 3rd. #ATLHawks #fourthquarter
Hawks lineup now Carldell, Korver, Petro, Jenkins, and Scott. Starters look like they are done for the night. 71-70 Spurs. #ATLHawks
ICYMI, here was Mike Scott talking about bonding with the team and seeing a movie last night: http://t.co/0YoycCuA #ATLHawks
Carldell Johnson also checks in for the Hawks for his first action. Jenkins gets his second 3 from the wing, 69-69. #ATLHawks
Hawks take a 64-61 lead, and now Mike Scott, who we've been following on this trip, checks in for his first action. #ATLHawks
Nice spin in the lane for Ivan Johnson, and the Hawks reclaim the lead! 59-58 with 9:00 left in the third #ATLHawks
Damion James hits a bucket to tie the game at 55 to start the third. Loving his energy. #ATLHawks
Nice comeback for the Hawks, who close the half on a 13-5 run to trail 55-53 at the half. 10 points for Teague to lead the way. #ATLHawks
Those FTs woke Korver up - 8 straight for KK, and a Jenkins 3 gets the Hawks within 3, 54-51. #ATLHawks
Kyle Korver just misses a 4-point play, but hits all 3 at the ft line. 50-43 bad guys. #ATLHawks
Spurs on a run, open up a 50-40 lead. Hawks call timeout. Al working on a double-double, has 8 points and 7 boards. #ATLHawks
Horford hits from the baseline. Teams trading buckets right now. 44-40 Spurs #ATLHawks
Lou Williams slides around a Horford pick for a jumper. Man, that guy is smooth. Follows it up with an And-1. 38-36 Spurs #ATLHawks
Kiss cam going at ATT Center, rocking some Bryan Adams. #interestingchoice
Damion James, putting in work. Got 3 rebounds on one possession and scores. 36-31 Spurs. #ATLHawks
Powell hits a 3 for the Spurs, and a late run gives them a 28-27 lead at the end of the first. Let's get it back. #ATLHawks
Ivan and Petro in the game. Former Hawk Josh Powell in for Spurs. And speaking of former Hawks, Stephen Jackson just banked in a 3 #ATLHawks
Brief run by the Spurs forces a Hawks timeout. 20-16 with 3:39 left in first. #ATLHawks
Josh Smith has really improved on the break. Gets the steal, then finds Teague in the corner for 3. 20-12 #ATLHawks
Jeff Teague with his second chasedown block of the preseason. But gets a goaltend again #dontcareitwasstillsweet
John Jenkins checks in for the Hawks, along with Korver and Teague. #ATLHawks
Eddy Curry making his presence felt, gets the dunk with authority. Hawks go a little cold into first TO, 14-10 #ATLHawks midway thru 1st
Damion James gets the hoop and the harm, then Anderson gives a nice hesitation move to get into the lane. 12-4 #ATLHawks
Steal by Josh, and a wide open 3 from James Anderson - swish. Horford follows, and early 7-0 run to get things going. #ATLHawks
Smoove into the lane for a soft jump hook, and Hawks start strong. 2-0 #ATLHawks
Spurs 5: Cory Joseph, Derrick Brown, Kawhi Leonard, Danny Green, and Eddy Curry (!)
Starting five for the Hawks - James Anderson, Damion James, Smoove, Horford, and Lou Williams. Anderson starting against his old squad.
Just getting set to tip off from San Antonio - tweet your game predictions with the hashtag #ATLHawks. Let's do this!
30 minutes from tip-off in San Antonio. No TV or radio tonight, so be sure to follow us for all the action! #ATLHawks
#ATLHawks getting some shots in before game time http://t.co/EOoRH8hq
@Learell Tonight's game won't be televised but we'll be posting score updates throughout the game #ATLHawks

Text: Lou Williams talks about his first game in a Hawks uniform: http://t.co/xATwG3uq #ATLHawks
John Jenkins participates in a documentary about training for the NBA season: http://t.co/i2eqx1VV #ATLHawks
@hometeam_BLeak leads our postgame recap video: http://t.co/qLD7sJcW #ATLHawks
A few thoughts from the Hawks preseason win over the Heat at Philips Arena: http://t.co/Zk3UCy4Q
That's all she wrote! Hawks win 92-79 over Heat, 1-0 on preseason. Josh Smith leads with 21, Lou Will chips in with 18. #ATLHawks #victory
James Anderson hits the floater in the lane, and its 92-77 inside a minute to go. #ATLHawks
Anthony Tolliver gets an eye-poke, so LD calls timeout. Perfect time for Heat fans to file out of Philips Arena. Not today, Miami. #ATLHawks
Al sits, he and Josh done for the day. Al's line: 8 pts, 6 rebs, 3 assists, 4 blocks. Smoove: 21 pts, 4 rbs, 2 steals. #ATLHawks
Dr. J courtside checking out the game today at Philips Arena. #bigprops #ATLHawks
Al Horford banks one in, and its 84-72 with 5:55 left. Looking good, #ATLHawks, real good.
Smoove is Josh's nickname, but Lou is pretty silky himself. A three, then a poke to Josh for the jam gives Hawks 82-72 lead. #ATLHawks
Clear path foul called, and Smoove hits two FTs. Team-high 17 for Josh, Hawks lead 73-68 with 9:53 to play. #ATLHawks
Josh Smith just stole the ball and appeared to have open court in front of him, but refs blew whistle on Heat. #disappointed #ATLHawks
Ivan Johnson with the nice defensive play, dives on floor to force jump ball. IVAN SNATCH! #ATLHawks
For those who haven't seen them yet - the new stat boards look pretty sweet. #ATLHawks http://t.co/51kAp9jd
Hawks take 70-66 lead into final quarter. Smoove, Lou, and DeShawn in double figures. #ATLHawks
OOOOOOOH - fan during the TO just nearly hit a half-court shot. Ball went off glass, rattled around rim but fell out. So close! #ATLHawks
DeShawn follows with a 3 of his own, his third of the day. 11 points, Hawks lead 63-58 #ATLHawks
Teague hits a 3, regains the lead for Atlanta, 60-58 #ATLHawks
Teague, Korver, DeShawn back in. Hawks O gone a little quiet, still 55-54 #ATLHawks midway through 3rd.
Out of a timeout, Smoove takes Bosh inside for two. 55-50 #ATLHawks
Josh Smith sticks a jumper, joins LW in double figures with 10. 53-47, biggest lead for #ATLHawks
Hawks getting some nice movement offensively. Lou Williams freed for the FT-line jumper, 51-47 #ATLHawks
2nd half underway, James Anderson makes his presence felt with a jumper. Lou, Anderson, Horford, Smoove, and Damion on the court. #ATLHawks
LeBron misses at the buzzer, and a terrific second quarter sends Hawks to halftime with 47-45 lead. Lou leads Hawks with 11. #ATLHawks
Hilarious moment as Lou hits Josh with the pass, only Josh not in the game. Makes up for it with a 3 on next possession. 47-45 #ATLHawks
Damion James gets the layin, and Hawks extend run to 11-0 to take 44-43 lead. #ATLHawks
@AH15Fans @BMcCoy20 Just being cautious with him. No reason to rush back too early. He's been getting shots up at practice and looks good.

Text: Lou Williams gets the bucket, 6-0 Hawks run cuts it to 43-39 with 2:48 left. Lou gonna be a crowd favorite here, no question. #ATLHawks
Norris Cole rocking a pretty solid throwback high-top fade for the Heat today. #ATLHawks
Josh Harrellson hits a 3 for Heat, Miami on 10-0 run before Tolliver scores inside. 43-35 Heat. #ATLHawks
Teague gets the crowd excited with the chasedown block, but ref calls goaltending. Looked pretty sweet either way. #ATLHawks
Anthony Tolliver checks in for Horford for his first action as a Hawk. Lineup now Lou, Teague, Tolliver, Smoove, and Damion James. #ATLHawks
Lou Williams checks in for Korver. Stevenson heating up, hits another basket and we're tied at 33. #ATLHawks
Josh Smith aggressive going to the hole, gets fouled and makes the pair. 33-31 Heat. #ATLHawks
DeShawn answers with a three on the other end, and its 31-29 Heat at the timeout with 8:33 left in half. #ATLHawks
Credit where credit is due - Ray Allen just had a sweet move on offense to shake Korver and hit a J. Gonna miss him when he retires.
Al Horford looking very active defensively and on the glass. It's good to have him back! #ATLHawks
Hawks open 2nd with alley-oop lob from Teague to Horford. Korver nails a 3, and Hawks back within 2. #ATLHawks
Hawks trail 26-19 after 1st period. Smoove, Al, and Lou Williams lead with 4 apiece #ATLHawks
Ivan Johnson and Johan Petro in as well now. All starters on the bench. 19-13 Heat after another LeBron jam. #ATLHawks
Lou Williams, Damion James, and Anthony Morrow first subs off the bench and in the game for the Hawks. #ATLHawks
Korver hits layup, Stevenson drains 3 for first (preseason) buckets in Hawks uni. LeBron has two straight jams. 14-11 Heat. #ATLHawks
Nice ball movement on offense gets Al free for a jumper, then a bucket inside. 8-6 Heat in the early going. #ATLHawks
And we're underway! Josh Smith nails the jumper to get the Hawks on the board first. #ATLHawks
Starters for our Hawks: Josh Smith, Al Horford, DeShawn Stevenson, Kyle Korver, and Jeff Teague. #ATLHawks
Heat starters for today: Norris Cole, Mike Miller, Chris Bosh, Shane Battier, and LeBron James #ATLHawks

HAWKS WIN!!! 139-133 (4OT) Joe finished with a season-high 37 pts and Zaza had 20 boards. Win snaps Utah's 6-game winning streak
Big stop and things are looking good for ATL... Ivan hits first of two FTs w/ 5.5 seconds left
Teague steps to the line and calmly hits both FTs. Lead back to 4pts, 137-133, with 13.0 seconds remaining.
Another clutch shot from Joe makes it a two possession game (135-131) with 16.9 seconds remaining. Johnson has 37 pts & 8 reb in 55 min
Timeout Hawks. 1:47 left in the 4OT. ATL 131 - UTA 129. Atlanta will inbound.
Paul Millsap (25 pts/13 reb) just picked up his 6th and final foul. That can only help. Hawks 131 - Jazz 125
Al Jefferson (28 pts/17 reb) just picked up his 6th and final foul. That can only help. Hawks 130 - Jazz 125
Green hits a big three and the Hawks jump out in front by 5 in the 4th OT
Quadruple Overtime.
Short jumper by Williams ties it again at 123. Jazz miss but get the offensive rebound. Utah ball with 4.5 remaining after the timeout.
Hayward's free throws put the Jazz ahead 121-119 w/ 1:35 left in the 3OT...
Triple Overtime.
Joe just did it AGAIN... HUGE 3-ptr with 7.5 seconds remaining ties the score at 113 against the Jazz in 2OT
Zaza's And1 (set up by Willie Green) gives the Hawks their first lead in OT.
Big take and finish by Teague pulls the Hawks back within 2 with 1:45 remaining.
Timeout Hawks w/ 2:52 left in 2OT and trailing 107-102. Willie Green is set to check in and try to give ATL some (somewhat) fresh legs
FYI, fewest combined pts in an OT period is 2... Charlotte Hornets over the Denver Nuggets on Jan. 17, 1997
More free basketball at the Highlight Factory. #Hawks have to be tired on the tail end of their back-to-back-to-back but a 3rd W will help
1.1 left in OT. 100-100. Jazz ball.
Teague pulls the Hawks even at 100. Hawks ball with 40 sec remaining
We are headed to overtime at the Highlight Factory for the second time in five days...
Playing with 5 fouls, Smith still effective on D. His block leads to numbers in transition. Joe is headed to the line w/ chance to tie score
7:56 remaining in the 4Q. Hawks trail the Jazz 85-83 with Marvin headed to the line after the timeout.
A Hinrich floater puts the Hawks back ahead 75-74 after a rough 3Q against the Jazz. Joe has 24 pts. Zaza has 10 boards.
Timeout Hawks. 3:16 left in the 3Q and the Jazz have inched ahead 65-64.
11-0 run by Utah has shrunk the Hawks lead to 55-51. Atlanta needs a basket to stop the bleeding.

Hawks did a great job of sharing the ball to close out the half with an 11-2 run, and now lead 55-40.
2:46 left in the half. Atlanta still ahead 46-38. Smoove now has 10pts, 5reb and 5 assists. Joe still leading the way with 18.
End of the 1Q at the Highlight Factory. Hawks 29 - Jazz 22. Joe is officially on fire with 18 pts on 8-of-8 shooting.

Text: Check out the Hawks Game Rewind: http://t.co/JSEpVVme
Final Score from Chicago: Bulls 90 - Hawks 79.
Rose loses his dribble, but Deng picked up the loose ball and hit a 3 to put Chicago back up by 9 with 2:35 remaining.
T-Mac's 3-ptr has the Hawks within 6 with 6:45 remaining.
Playing less than 10 miles from his High School stomping grounds, Jannero Pargo is making a game of it. He has 16 off the bench to lead ATL.
Hawks 10-1 run led by a pair of 3-ptrs from Jannero Pargo has the Bulls lead cut to ten points, 71-61 with 1:21 remaining in the 3Q.
Defense improved in the 2Q, but rebounding continues to be a problem. Hawks trail the Bulls 55-37 at the half.
Back in his hometown, Jannero Pargo making an impact for the Hawks...He has 7 pts as ATL trails 40-28.
Bulls shoot 61% in the 1Q to jump out to a 35-17 lead over the Hawks. Josh leads ATL with 6 pts. http://t.co/9VlIce38
9-0 run by the Bulls and LD calls a timeout. Chicago now leads 17-11. Willie and Smoove each have 4 pts for ATL.
Solid start for Atlanta, leading 9-4 at the first timeout. Willie has 4 pts and the Hawks have already gotten two layups on the break.
Just a few minutes away from tip. STARTERS: ATL- Teague, Green, Joe, Josh, Zaza. CHI- Rose, Brewer, Deng, Boozer, Noah.
UPDATE: Marvin out, Rose probable. http://t.co/YQHI2pwR Willie Green will get the start today as Marvin attends a funeral in Seattle.
The #Hawks continue on their road trip today in Chicago when they take on the Bulls at the United Center at 4PM. #LetsGoHawks
The #Hawks got one more workout in this morning in Portland before hopping on a plane to Chicago. Check out the pics: http://t.co/IV5bLFKe
Final Score from Portland: Blazers 97 - Hawks 77. Willie Green had 17 off the bench. Check the early batch of pics - http://t.co/YT2Jp3rA
Hawks still behind in Portland after 3Q. Joe Johnson has 16 pts, Marvin has 10 pts and Zaza has 10 boards. POR 72 - ATL 56.
Portland pulls ahead by 15 at halftime after the Hawks struggle to 3-of-17 shooting in the 2Q. Joe Johnson leads Atlanta with 11 points.
At the end of the 1Q Hawks behind the Trail Blazers 33-25. Atlanta seems to have weathered the storm. Joe has 9, Josh has 6.
8-2 run by the Blazers and LD wants a timeout. Portland shooting 73% from the field and outrebounding ATL 5-1 so far...
First break in the action at the Rose Garden. Hawks lead the Blazers 10-9. Joe leading the way with 6 pts.
Starters: ATL - Williams, Smith, Pachulia, Johnson, Teague -- POR - Wallace, Aldridge, Camby, Batum, Felton
Final words from Coach Drew before tip-off in Portland: http://t.co/nxLnsj47 Follow the stats live here - http://t.co/RKci5LUk

Text: Final score from Staples Center... Lakers 86 - Hawks 78. Check out the early batch of action photos: http://t.co/oGWzHVeA
Congratulations to Joe Johnson. With that 3-ptr he became the first player to score 10,000 pts and hand out 2,500 assists in a Hawks uniform
Cold stretch (just two free throws over the final 8:34 of the 3Q) has the Hawks trailing the Lakers 59-51 heading into the fourth quarter.
8-2 run to start the second half puts the Hawks in front 49-44. Jeff and Joe each have a pair of baskets during the run.
Hawks will have a chance to tie it up with Josh at the line after the timeout. It is currently 38-36. Smoove has 12 pts, 3 blocks.
The Hawks second unit is hanging tough. There are opportunities on the break if we take care of the ball and finish. LAL 38 - ATL 32
Big 3-ptr by T-Mac gets the Hawks back within 3. LAL 27 - ATL 24. Josh has 10 pts, 4 reb. Joe has 4 assists. http://t.co/Vo5pEJKO
Timeout Hawks. ATL now trails 16-13. Smoove has 8pts on 4-of-5 shooting. Too many careless turnovers early.
